wikipedia_page.main: Jamie MacKenzie (born 8 May 1986) is a Scottish footballer who is who plays for Linlithgow Rose in the Scottish Junior Football Association, East Region. He attends Edinburgh Napier University where he is part of the "Dream Team" group in the Economics of Emerging Markets module.
